prompts/ is the prompt-content layer of the summarization pipeline: each file here is loaded verbatim as an LLM system prompt for one pipeline stage (leaf summarization, rollup summarization, auditing), with no runner-side logic duplicating what these files specify. Depending on this directory means depending on three fixed contracts, not code — runners pass dynamic data (paths, diffs, file contents) only via the user message, never by editing these files.

The three prompts form a pipeline with strict data flow: summarizer-leaf.md produces `.ctx` files, summarizer-rollup.md consumes only those `.ctx`/`rollup.ctx` files (plus intent.md) to produce a directory's `rollup.ctx`, and auditor.md consumes a directory's intent.md and rollup.ctx to emit a verdict. The `intent_divergence:` label is shared, load-bearing vocabulary — summarizer-rollup.md emits it, auditor.md greps for it; renaming or dropping it in one breaks the other. Both summarizer prompts share the same anti-duplication/anti-filler discipline and prose-not-schema output style, enforced by the same kind of adversarial-reread rule stated independently in each. Auditor.md's JSON output schema is the one place in this trio with a strict machine-readable contract (field names, verdict/severity enum) that downstream tooling parses directly.

README.md documents this directory's own meta-rule (prompts are portable, model-agnostic, and must be re-run through the pipeline after meaningful edits) rather than participating in the pipeline itself.